      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVINE SECRETS (6) missed a nose here over 1300m off an easy win at Canberra and then didn't have much luck over 1400m at Rosehill from a wide gate. Draws inside today and is poised to post her third win for a leading metro stable. SMASHING TIME (1) resumes for a local Price yard and has won 2/4 fresh and 2/3 this course/distance. Brings an easy trial win at the track and has a handy 3kg claim back in grade. Draws low and he's feared. PRESIDES (2) resumes for the local Beer-Carpenter barn and has been contesting stronger races. Has prepared with a comfortable trial win and has placed 2/3 fresh. The tongue tie is applied for the first time and it won't surprise if he uses the inside gate to advantage. BUTTERFLY STYLE (4) performs fresh and has trialled here. She won't be far away.",
